theorem Topology.P1_of_P1_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 (X := X) (closure A) → Topology.P1 (X := X) A := by
  intro hP1Cl
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1Cl ⊢
  intro x hxA
  -- First, regard `x` as an element of `closure A`.
  have hxClA : (x : X) ∈ closure A := subset_closure hxA
  -- Apply `P1` for `closure A`.
  have hxClIntClA : x ∈ closure (interior (closure A)) := hP1Cl hxClA
  -- Rewrite with the equality
  --   `closure (interior (closure A)) = closure (interior A)`.
  have h_eq :=
    Topology.closure_interior_closure_interior_eq_closure_interior
      (X := X) (A := A)
  simpa [h_eq] using hxClIntClA

replace theorem Topology.P1_closure_of_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 (X := X) A → Topology.P1 (X := X) (closure A) := by
  intro hP1
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1 ⊢
  intro x hxClA
  -- Step 1:  from `P1` we get `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have h₁ : closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
    have : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := hP1
    simpa [closure_closure] using closure_mono this
  have hxClIntA : x ∈ closure (interior A) := h₁ hxClA
  -- Step 2:  monotonicity of `interior` gives `interior A ⊆ interior (closure A)`,
  -- and taking closures preserves inclusions.
  have h₂ : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
    have hInt : interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
      interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
    exact closure_mono hInt
  -- Combine the two inclusions to finish.
  exact h₂ hxClIntA

theorem Topology.interior_closure_inter_closure_subset_inter_interior_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure (A ∩ closure B)) ⊆
      interior (closure A) ∩ interior (closure B) := by
  intro x hx
  have hxA : x ∈ interior (closure A) := by
    -- `A ∩ closure B ⊆ A`, hence the same holds for their closures.
    have h_subset : closure (A ∩ closure B) ⊆ closure A := by
      apply closure_mono
      intro y hy
      exact hy.1
    exact (interior_mono h_subset) hx
  have hxB : x ∈ interior (closure B) := by
    -- `A ∩ closure B ⊆ closure B`.
    have h_subset : closure (A ∩ closure B) ⊆ closure B := by
      apply closure_mono
      intro y hy
      exact hy.2
    exact (interior_mono h_subset) hx
  exact And.intro hxA hxB

theorem Topology.closure_diff_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A \ B : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
  -- `A \ B` is contained in `A`, so the monotonicity of `closure` gives the result.
  exact closure_mono (by
    intro x hx
    exact hx.1)
